			4.3 New Dataset: Word Similarity in Context.
			The many previous datasets that associate human judgments on similarity between pairs of words, such as WordSim-353, MC (Miller and Charles, 1991) and RG (Rubenstein and Goodenough, 1965),have helped to advance the development of vector space models.
			However, common to all datasets is that similarity scores are given to pairs of words inisolation.
			This is problematic because the mean ings of homonymous and polysemous words depend highly on the words?
			contexts.
